parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder leaks can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a decrease in braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks from the master cylinder
spongy brake pedal
low brake pedal
brake warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake lights stay on or do not turn on
faulty brake light switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failed brake shoes can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed brake motor can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loss of braking power
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
brake warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed power brake system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
low brake pedal
loss of braking power
brake warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Cruise Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without input from the driver
the cruise control becomes stuck
and the vehicle fails to respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle control motor can cause the engine to rev excessively, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The engine revs extremely high when shifting into gear
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration
and the idle control motor fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to fail to respond to acceleration input, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to operate when applying the accelerator
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
and the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stuck or difficult to turn, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stuck or difficult to turn
increased steering effort
especially during cold weather
jerky or hard steering when the vehicle first starts
cold power steering.
